consider two settings for the strange quark\nchemical potentials (I) $\\mu_s=\\mu_B/3$ and (II) $\\mu_s=0$. The isentropic\ntrajectories of the QGP matter are compared for these two cases. The phase\ndiagram of DQPM-CP is close to PNJL calculations. The leading order pQCD\ntransport coefficients of both approaches differ. This elucidates that the\nknowledge of the phase diagram alone is not sufficient to describe the\ndynamical evolution of QGP.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 19 Aug 2021 09:07:24 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 29 Oct 2021 13:58:55 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Wed, 2 Feb 2022 11:50:26 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-03-23"}
