antage of this\nmethod is to avoid the diagonalization of a large QRPA matrix, especially at\nfinite temperature where the size of configuration space is significantly\nincreased. The implementation of the linear response code is used to study the\ntemperature evolution of IAR, GTR, and spin-dipole resonance (SDR) in even-even\ntin isotopes in the temperature range $T = 0 - 1.5$ MeV.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 19 Aug 2021 14:15:25 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-12-15"}
